\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And what year you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Chertsey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And can you remember the year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 How old are you now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 I'm eighty-three in twenty-second of March.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Next March - in 1970?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 So you're eighty-two now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Eighty-two now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Taunton, - Somerset. Came to Guildford in - when I was eight years of age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 How many years did you live in the house where you were born - can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh, I don't know. I don't think I could get that for you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 That was in Taunton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes, Somerset. I think it was on the state - my father was electrician for the for the town - you know - electric light works in Taunt
on. And I came to Guildford when I was eight - they brought me up to Guildford. Then the whole family came up to work for his relations were here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 What street did you live in in Taunton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, I think it - St James's Street I think it was - I wouldn't say to be honest but I think so. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And how long did you live in the house in Guildford?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh well, I - I was there until I went into service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Was that in Guildford?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes. I've been in Guildford all my time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 When you came to Guildford first where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 High Path Road. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And were you there until you went into service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Service - yes. I went to school there. Meadow school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Do you remember why your family moved to Guildford?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 To come t
o relations my - my father came to work for his broth - well, his sister's husband. To run his electric light plant for him. A - at Dungeness - he took that - my uncle Oliver took Dungeness on for twenty-one years and then he - well, I should think it was
 
up - as near as I can remember they would be there about six-seven years - somewhere along there - my aunt got tired of the country life - uncle was a big sports man. And there was another uncle which was the gamekeeper for - for the same uncle - the one 
as - that little cottage is still there now 'cos the woman that's in it comes to our flat - yes, and that's the Taunton Lodge. Yes. That's where my - my other - father's other sister lived - 'cos he was a gamekeeper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 One dead and I've got one, two, three, one, two brothers and one, four sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 You've got two brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Living. And four sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And one brother died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes. And he .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And where did you come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 In between
 the two of - he would have been - if he'd have been alive he would have been nearly - nearly eighty - what would he be - three years older than me - about eighty-five he would have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Which was the eldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 He was the eldest. And he went to t
he Boer War - yes. You see, the Boer War was over and he lived in High Path Road - Queen Victoria died when we were in High Path Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 So he would have been eighty-three now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes, he would have been eighty-three - well, wait a minute - no - I - yes he would be I suppose because I'm eighty-three in March.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And then your - who came next to you a brother or a sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Er - another brother - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And how much younger was he than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, there was - there's one sister dead too, 
I didn't tell you that did I. He well, he come in between me - he'd be eighteen months younger than me and then there was a girl eighteen months younger than him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And then there'd be another girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Er - no, another boy and then - there was - finished up there was one, two, three girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And how much difference between them in age - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, I got a sister now that\rquote 
s been there Sir Dennis Ford these past times and - and Deaconess Ford - they passed away and she's got her own
 bungalow which she had built for her up in Beach Lane in Guildford. She's seventy - she now - seventy - see - er - that sort of thing goes from you - but she'd be seventy - eight - seventy-nine she'd be - seventy-nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 So would you say that - you said that your eldest brother was only a little older than you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 About eighteen months or two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, may have been two years older - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And then eighteen months between you and your next brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And - they - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And about eighteen months between him and your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Months between that girl - they - most some of them were eighteen months to two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Were most of them like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Was there a big gap between any of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No, no big gap at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Do you remember how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 When I was born - he was coming ninety when he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 You don't remember what year that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, see, dates I can't keep dates in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Where did he come from - was he a Taunton man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes he was - he was born in Taunton - he was a Taunton man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And he was an electrician?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes he was electrician for the town of Taunton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did he have another job before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well I wouldn't know - wouldn't know about that would I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Afterwards did he keep the same job or did he change?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh he was always electrician - he never - he was man had - believed in one man one job - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did he do any other jobs part time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No. No, no. Nothing. He - electrician - electricity and nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Do you ever remember your father being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
Only when they changed over - when my uncle and aunt got - tired of the country and - well, he didn't but she did got tired of country life - then th
ere was a gap but of course it made no difference to him because uncle kept him going until he got in the other job you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633140\charrsid10685554 
'Cos they went back to London and the gentleman there - see he took the lease on at - tied him for twenty-one years - well then a g
entleman named Lawley took over the lease from Uncle Oliver which set him free you see and they went to Leight - Leighton Court Road in London then, see, and uncle had - he had the Cross Keys Blackfriar's Bridge and he had a pub at Havelock Arms, Meeting 
H
ouse Lane, but you see it was a family business - he was - you didn't have to be a relation when visitors came - understand what I mean - when visitors came he was Mr Farmey but - other electricians - Mr Farley when visitors came but when they were away i
t was your brother. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
He was her brother yes. And they could go up to the house as much as he liked the same as my other uncle the one that was gamekeeper he was - would be the same you see, he could go up when he liked to - perhaps not with visitors.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 You don't know how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No. I don't know that you see - I couldn't tell you any at all. You see she's my father }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403139 
Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554  twice - this last mother was my step-mother. You see - my mother - my mother - in Taunton died - when - oh I couldn't tell you how old I was exactly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 How many children did she have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
There'd be one - there was one, two, three - four of the first and four of the second. My sister that's in Guildford here is really - and of course we've always been a united family - is really a step-sister. Really - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Do you know where your mother came from? Was she born in Taunton or did she move?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 I think she must have lived outside of Taunton when my dad }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403139 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554  her. I think so - I can't remember that. Her name was Turley - I know that because we - we had some china with her name on - that's all I can tell you about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did she ever talk about any work she did before she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403139 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did she work after she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403139 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Not to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did she do any part time work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Can you remember how many rooms there were in the house that you lived in Taunton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Sitting room and - oh in Taunton - well, it would be a six roomed house just the same we always had a six roomed house - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did that mean there were two sitting rooms and four bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 It was the front room, kitchen and scullery in those days - they were always called that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And how many bedrooms then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Three. In each case - in Taunton and Guildford - High Path Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No, no-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No lodgers, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Do you remember if your mother paid anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
No, never. She always did her own work - right up 'til she died - she died suddenly. She did all her own work - she never had no help. Well, there was no help in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 So your mother did all her own duties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did she do the cleaning and looking after the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes, everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh it was all done at home, in every case, my mother always - and my step-mother - they always did all their own washing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 How old were you when your mother died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
Can't seem to remember nothing about that - gone now. We were eight you see and of course - she'd been dead several years - I come up to the town when I was eight - I should think it must have been 
when - round about six I would - I should think. Probably too young to think ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 So your father re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403139 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 ?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Father had - he re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403139 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
 - and he had a young family you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 In Taunton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes. He }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403139 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
 in Taunton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Do you remember if your mother or step-mother made the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes, they did all their own - clothes making and everything - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Were the clothes new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh, new, everything - and they just - my - my mother used to cut up my dad's trousers and make the boys trousers - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And what about your father - did he make any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
Oh, he was just electrician - he did nothing else. Except his garden and his house and all that you know, you see - he was - he was a spotless man and very p
roud where - in his garden and all that. But - no - no work outside - he was a man that said one man one job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 What about shoes - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh, my dad used to mend out shoes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Where would they be bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, of course - yes - at the shop - mm - they'd go the leather shop and buy the pieces of leather and he'd repair them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 It must have been quite a job to provide shoes for all your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh, oh yes, well we were a family of eight you see, were four girls and four boys
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Were the shoes always new? Or did you sometimes have second hand ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh no, always new, and as they wore he'd repair them. No, they - they didn't - there was - no such thing as second hand in those ....

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did you pass them on from one child to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes, what one child wore - got too small for him the other one took on - it was not like today - my goodness not.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes, he was very - very - methodical in that way. He'd do anything in the house for - to help her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did he do any cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes, he would do any cleaning or help with the meals and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, he did if she was laid up of course. But they never had any help they always did their jobs themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did he help with the washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
Well, there I couldn't say about that but I'm - still on the average - us children as we grew up we had to work - we had to do it you see - we had to clean the knives and wash up and all sorts of jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 What about the fires - do you remember who did the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh well, my dad used to go light the fires - he was able to like - according to his time of going to work you see in the winter tim
e you would use a lot of light don't you and he'd have to go to his job very early you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 If he was at home he would light the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 He would do it - oh yes, he would do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 If he was out then your mother would light them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes - would light it yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 What about decorating - do you remember if he did any decorating in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
No, I don't think he did any decorating - I think probably my mother did most of that or got somebody just to give her a hand you know. People were 
in those days were really neighbourly. Not like today - no they were very neighbourly and good to one - they used to help one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 What about repairs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh - he'd do any - yes, he'd do any little job like - unless it was a big job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Would that include any improvements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
No, they - they were old fashioned cottages in those days - there were no improvements. He used to have an ordinary bungalow bath you see - no bathroom - nothing in like that - no - not until later years you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did your father ever help with the children? Did he ever dress you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
I don't know about having to dress us - he was very good. Yes, he was a very happy man - he - always he liked to have a Sunday night gather the children about and have a little sing with them of a Sunday - yes, oh yes. He was very good with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did he ever bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No, I don't think he did that - I think mother kept her own jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did he read to you and tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes, he did that sort of thing - used to tell us funny stories and funny tales yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did he ever take you out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh we - we used to go out together - all across the downs and that - right around Newland Corner and all that of a Sunday evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Would that be with your mother too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh, all together - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did he ever take you out when she was busy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh no, not that - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did he ever look after you at home when she was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes, he'd stay in if he was at home you see, he'd look after the chil
dren while she was shopping but they used - mostly be together - they were a couple that where one went the other went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did you have any task that you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No, because - by - when the
 - when my sister was born - because she's twelve years the sister that lives in Guildford - she's away at the moment - she is twelve years younger than me and I used to have to take her out and help with her - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And how long did you continue to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
You used to leave school at thirteen years of age you did in them days and - there was no so - restriction of school - because - I didn't have the full amount of schooling because I often out with my gran and that and she was fond of - handsom
e cab - and she went out for a drive - well, she took me with her - see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 So you might miss school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, oh yes, if I went a drive I'd miss school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 You wouldn't mind that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Not a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 After you left school did you still help at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
Well, no, 'cos I went out in the - the bottom of High Path Road there was a - a person named Mrs Chandler - she had one of those high houses on the main road, like down the bottom of High Path and she had of - young children and I started there t
o help her with her baby - you see - because it was close to home and it was a kind of mothers help I was then you see, and - he was - he was - he used to work for a Peak Frean}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633140\charrsid10685554 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 s and Doctor D. Jersey that lived in - in Waterden Road he used to have a room 
there for practice, see, so he - her hands were rather full so I used to be a mothers help. That was just starting of my - doing - going out to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did your brothers and sisters help with the children as well - would they take one out in a pram as you say you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, they were close on one another you see, there wasn't the gap of years between them I don't think they did much in that way you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Would they help to dress them or bath them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh we used to dress one another - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And feed them at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh no, mother did the feeding - she used to like to know what they had to eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did the younger children help the older children in any way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, no I don't think so - no. It was just a natural child life we had you see we were a very happy family - very happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes. We never - we weren't allowed to be out after eight o'clock at night in the summer - off to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did your mother put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh we - well, when we were big enough we'd put ourselves in bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 When you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh very tiny - she would do it. When we - we were brought up to help ourselves. We weren't brought up to be nursed. We had to help 
ourselves and brought up to to work - to know what work meant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 If your mother didn't put you to bed it meant you were old enough to put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Put yourselves - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 But nobody else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No, no. No-one else - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Do you remember how old you were when you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No, I can't remember that. I know how old I was when I went out - I'll tell you to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Can you remember how old some of your younger sisters were when they put themselves to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Can you remember how the family slept?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
Oh we had - mother and father had their room and the boys had their room and the girls had their room. They were all brought up from babies to know that they - had to sleep on their own like you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh, down in the kitchen. By the fire in the winter and out in the scullery in the summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 How often did you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh well, w
hen they were dirty we used to put our off - and if we were playing and got dirty we had clean clothes on. Naturally when you bath you change all your clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And put on clean clothes the next morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Were there any occasions when they ate in another room?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No. Always in the kitchen. The sitting room was kept as a sitting room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 In the scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And what did she cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, the gas - they was always gas - yes - but we used to have candles and little lamps to go to bed with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 She didn't have a coal range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh we had a - we had a - a stove that had a - side oven in the kitchen. Sometimes if sh
e didn't use the gas she would use that - yes. She had both. And there was a little boiler at the side that she turned a tap on to get up water - side of the oven - well, the oven was one side and the tap that side and the fire there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Would that be enough for your bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes. Yes. Quite enough. And it would boil if you had a good fire you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 That was very convenient?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 When was breakfast eaten - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, the children - well that all depends you see they had to get to school by nine o'clock - we would have our breakfast about eight.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 How many members of the family would be present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, we all had our breakfast - meals together you see, except my dad and he was away all day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Your dad would have gone by that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
Oh yes, he would have gone - he used to - he had to walk right across them there Downs - used to have to - there weren't no cars and hiring in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And what would he have before he went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh well, he -
 he didn't have a cooked breakfast - he probably - then of course he used to go in down my other uncles and they'd cook a snack in there for him. 'Cos they were family you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 What did you usually have for breakfast - do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well
, we generally had porridge and then we had - a bit of something afterwards. Sometimes an egg or - perhaps a rasher of bacon or - something like that but - a bit of fish - just all depends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 What would you drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh, tea for breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And did you have anything different on certain days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No. We never had anything different - only when we had a party and that was a birthday party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes, Sunday we used to have a cooked breakfast always - tomatoes and eggs 
and sausages and all that kind of thing. Yes. And a roast dinner on a Sunday. My dad always used to carve the joint and he used to say lovely joint you know, in those days - he'd do all the carving.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And what would you have for your mid-day meal - can you remember at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 What do you mean - on a Sunday or weekday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 On a week day first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
Well, only average I suppose, same as you would now, just - well, what can I say ordinary - we sometimes had a steak and kidney pudding - you'd go to the shop and buy sixpennyworth of pieces in those days and two pen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7633140\charrsid10685554 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633140\charrsid10685554 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
th of kidney and a pen'orth of suet and you'd have a lovely great pudding for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 That would be a main meal in the middle of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 That - yes - that would be a main meal in the middle of the day and that would feed a family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And you'd come back from school for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
Yes, we'd come back from school. And then they'd save my dad's for his dinner - didn't cook again - saved my dad's on a plate over a saucepan of water and get it hot you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 That was in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 That was his tea - that was his dinner for tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And what did you have for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh, bread, butter and jam and cake and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Anything else before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 W
ell, we'd have a cup of cocoa or something of that before we went to bed you see. But - nothing - you see - you realized you didn't get the money in those days - money was very small - I don't know exactly - I know what my husband's money was - when he wa
s alive - but I don't know about my dad's 'cos I couldn't remember about that but all the way through - very little money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And you were a big family too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes. Of eight children you see, four boys and four girls. And - there was quite a keep you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 On Sundays you had a joint?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes, always a joint on a Sunday. A nice big joint - yes. Batter pudding, roas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7633140\charrsid10685554 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554  potatoes and - and a cabbage and - and generally an apple tart or whatever fruit was in season.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 What about tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes, mot
her would be busy Sunday mornings making - what pastry she had left she'd make - often little things for tea you see and the next day. Special tea on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And then the same when you went to bed - a drink of cocoa?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes, yes, something like that - just the ordinary natural feeding you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh no, she didn't do that - no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And your father didn't bake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No. He used to take the dough and that to the bake}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633140\charrsid10685554  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 house and have a dough cake - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes, 'cos we had a garden with a lot of fruit you see, we were never short of jam - she made all her own jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Do you remember if she bottle any fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes, she used to bottle plums and damsons and all that
 sort of thing. And we had grapes going round the house but we didn't bottle them - used to eat them. Open the window and pick half a bunch of - they grew upstairs sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Would she bottle any vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No, well she used to salt down beans sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did she ever make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes she pickled onions. My dad was very fond of pickled onions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 What about home made wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, no, they didn't make those - I made it myself when I were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403139 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554  but he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did she make any herbal remedies for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633140\charrsid10685554 Oh well her idea was Ep}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
som salts and - sulphur and - sulphur and treacle we used to have a spoonful of sulphur and treacle - yes - well that was if you were out of order you see - out of order she'd mix up some treacle and sulphur and give you that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 You mean if you were constipated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes, oh yes. If you felt out of order in any way - any way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did she ever brew any beer for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did your father or mother grow their own vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes, they did that, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did they have to buy any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No, I - I think he used to grow enough to last round to the come again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Do you remember if they bought any tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, I exp
ect mother kept that in store because she used to open a tin of peaches or that sometimes so she bound to have had that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 So she'd have some tins in her store cupboard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did they keep any livestock such as hen, or pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 We had pigs. We had pigs - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did you have goats?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No, no, no goats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And no hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No, neither - pigs weren't in High Path Road - pigs was when they moved from High Path Road over to Wallhurst.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well that w
as - the first day - my father died in Malvern you see - but when he left Merrill you see he had to go - had another job as I told you - well, they went over to Wallhurst - this house they were in at Barnet Lane - that's where he kept pigs that's where he
 had such a big garden and that's where they grew all their own vegetables and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Was that before you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403139 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes, I wasn't - I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9403139 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554  in 1915.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And you lived in Wonersh did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No, no, I was - I was in service i
n Guildford - I was at where I told you I went first off as the mothers help from there I went to Mr Chennel that used to be the baker in Guildford - well there out of date years and years ago - the Chennel's - while not at the bakers but at their private
 
house - she used to do - take in boarders and - in Churchill Road - and I used to have to wait table and all that sort of thing. Mrs Chennel used to do all her own cooking and everything. I had to do - wait table and help with the housework - all that - t
hat was my second job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Can you remember how many times a week you would eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, every day I eat meat. Of some sort - or fish - meat or fish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did you ever get any extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes, we used to have 
a lot of rabbits. 'Cos of course they had rabbits there used to get them off the gamekeeper. Oh used to have a lot of rabbits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 So you didn't get them from anybody poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh no, no. From the estate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Do you ever remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
No. There was always - she was a wonderful manager - there was always plenty - for either - she used to believe in a lot of suet puddings and boiled rice and all that sort of thing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Would your father have a larger helping than the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
Oh no, he'd have what he wanted and we would all have what we wanted - we could have more if we wanted it. Always had plenty - always a good food going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Do you remember if you were allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
Oh no - my father was very strict. Yes, they were very strict at the table. You weren't allowed to get up like they do these days and run about and all that so - oh no, they was - he was very sincere with everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No, we had to eat what was put before us. No picking and choosing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on your plate?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh we didn't leave it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt could you ask someone to pass it or did you have to wait until it was offered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes, you wouldn't get up and grab it yourself - you'd ask one of the others that were near it to pass it to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 You didn't have to wait until it was offered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh no. They'd pass it when you asked if they weren't using it themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, the proper way of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes. Sit at the table until you'd finished - mightn't leave the table unless you'd properly .......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Could you bring toys or a booked to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No. Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 When you'd finished your meals and by asking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 You asked if you could get down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes, may I leave the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 If they were home - yes, yes, all together if they were home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Your father too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes, if they were home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did you always have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, on the average there wasn't much to choose from - always sat down -
 there was only room for all - unless - somewhere round the table like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 But would you sit in the same place round the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh we weren't fussy like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 It didn't matter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No; So long as we sat at the table and behaved ourselves - a
ll right. Always a cane hanging over the picture - a cane - yes - my dad always had a cane hanging over the picture. If you didn't behave yourself you had a wallop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Who would serve the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh well, mother serve and then where there was a joint dad carved you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 In what order would you be served?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
Well, there - eldest generally seemed to come in first as you come down like and and the baby - well there'd be generally one mother would feed you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Would your father have the first helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
Well, no, not on the average I don't think he - they - he was - he generally carved out for the family like you see. Mainly - yes. Oh if it was a pudding and that it was according to how you ate your meal if you'd ate mother would serve y
ou - you didn't sit and wait. See she'd serve you with your pudding if you'd finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Where would your younger brothers and sisters sit before they could feed themselves Would they sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh - well, they generally - mother generally 
- fed them - I'd say - either afterwards or before - sometimes she fed them before then they would sit in the chair while the others were feeding you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Would she always feed them or would one of the others feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh - oh no, she would do everything herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 How old would they be when they were old enough to join in the family meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh - I should think they were - well, I should say from two years of age they would be feeding themselves you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 And then they would be joining the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes. They joined the family soon as they could feed themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes. Easy - very kind and good but very strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did you feel close to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Yes, we were a very united fa
mily - oh very happy - we never quarrelled one with the other. Well, my dad wouldn't allow it - the cane would come down you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did she show affection to her children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes, she were very fond of all her children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 If you had any worries could you share them with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh we didn't get any in them days you see - you - not when we were young like that
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 What about your father - could you talk to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, he just used to there with the family talk all together sort of thing 
you know really. There was nothing secret - sort of - everything was open you see, there was nothing .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Was he interested in what you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 He was always interested in his family. Yes. Very interested.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did he show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh yes, he was a wonderful father - wonderful. And he lived wonderfully easy and he was no trouble whatever - he slept his life out.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 If you had any worries could you talk to your father about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well you could have done if you'd had them but I don't know as we had them. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
Well, you had to - be very - united all together - happy - you didn't - you weren't allowed to quarrel about you see. As I said there was always a cane over a picture - if you didn't behave yourself you had it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No, only natural. Just natural - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did they say that you should hit back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh no, they didn't tell us that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 If another child hurt you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No, they didn't tell us that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, they never had any trouble with any of us - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
We went to Sunday school and all that sort of thing - we had to keep Sunday as a Sunday - went to Sunday school and - and - we had to be in at the proper time and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Would they think that some things were right and some things were wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 No - well - of course it was - I don't know as we done anything - there was anything we used to come - sort of come against like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 What about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh I don't know as we weren't allowed to swear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 You weren't allowed to swear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
No. No, it was a thing out of the - out of it altogether. Proper talking - proper everything. They were old fashioned in all their ways. But kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 When the grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Oh no, we didn't butt in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 Well, I can't remember that we did anything - we weren't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13781051 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 But you would be caned if you were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5578324 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14308090\charrsid10685554 
We - we - yes - a cane was always there on a picture for us. We knew that we should get it if we didn't behave ourselves and do as we should do.
